The conditonal operator is also known as ternary operator.
The statement are the decision-making statements which depends upon the output of the expression.
It  is represented by two symbols, i.e. '?' and ':'.
As conditional operator works on three operands so it is also known as the ternary operator.
Syntax of a conditional operator
Expression1?Expression2:Expression3;

Example
#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
int a,b,c,d;
printf("Enter 3 numbers=");
scanf("%d%d%d",&a,&b,&c);
d=(a>b)?((a>c)?a:c):((b>c)?b:c);
printf("Largest number=%d",d);
return 0;
}
